gov.usgs.anss.edgeoutput

Class TraceBuf

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.edge.TimeSeriesBlock
      • gov.usgs.anss.edgeoutput.TraceBuf
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<TimeSeriesBlock>

    public final class TraceBuf
extends TimeSeriesBlock
    represents a Earthworm Trace Buf packet. It has a binary buffer of byes and ByteBuffer wrapper for manipulation and byte swapping. It implements the TimeSeriesBlock interface so it can be used anywhere generalized time series objects are desired - in particular they can be stored in ChannelHolders. 
     The header on the wire is :
 0   msgInst    Message institution
 1   msgType    A type of message
 2   modId      A module ID
 3   fragNum    The packet number of the packet, 0=first
 4   msgSeqNum  The message sequence number
 5   lastOfMsg  Flag indicating this is the last packet in the message
 Trace buffers
 0 int    pinno
 4 int    nsamp
 8 double starttime
 16 double endtime
 24 double samprate
 32 char[7] station
 39 char[9] network
 48 char[5] chan      // Non-version 2.0
 52 char[3] loc
 55 char[2] version   // '2' and '0' if version 2.0, otherwise 1.0 assumed
 57 char[3] data type
 60 char[2] quality
 62 char[2] pad

      • setData

        public void setData(java.lang.String seedname,
                    long start,
                    int nsamp,
                    double rate,
                    int[] samples,
                    int off,
                    int institution,
                    int module,
                    int seqno,
                    int pinno)
        set data in this tracebuf - this is used so a tracebuf can be reused by updating its contents and not allocating new memory. The trace buf type is set based on the scn flag (see setSCNMode). If the flag is set the trace buf will be SCN type, if the flag is not set it will be a type 2 SNCL packet.
        Parameters:
        seedname - The 12 character seed name
        start - the milliseconds since 1970 of the start time
        nsamp - the number of data samples.
        rate - The data rate in Hz
        samples - array of 32 bit ints with the time series
        off - The offset into the samples for the start of data
        institution - The institution code to set
        module - The module number
        seqno - The sequence number of the sample (will be 8 bit when done)
        pinno - The PINNO for this channel
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the array in is bigger than the tracebuf size

      • setData

        public void setData(byte[] inbuf)
             throws java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException
        set data in this tracebuf - this is used so a tracebuf can be reused by updating its contents and not allocating new memory. If the data buffer has version '2' (dec 50) set, then the scn flag for this TraceBuf is set. Note : This can lead to inadvertant changes of SCN flag if this packet is reused for other set data. Only use this routine for packets whose type is known to be right To convert between formats it is better to use the "setData(seedname, etc) which will retain the SCN setting. The length is assumed to be the length of the buffer.
        Parameters:
        inbuf - The byte buffer to use to replace data in this TraceBuf
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the array in is bigger than the tracebuf size

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(TraceBuf o)
        Compare this TraceBuf object to another. First the two objects' SEED names are compared, and if they are equal, their starting dates are compared. If the object is "cleared", then it always sorts later.
        Parameters:
        o - the other MiniSeed object
        Returns:
        -1 if this object is less than other, 0 if the two objects are equal, and +1 if this object is greater than other.
